Requirements:
Following cpan modules
Nagios::Plugin
Nagios::Plugin::DieNicely
XML::LibXML
File::Basename
LWP::UserAgent

Install:
solace.cfg defines the commands.you might want to modify this to set threshold for all the system directly in the command alias.
for example with the environemnt check,setting NPU warning to 90 and critical to 110, for ALL systems, change:
define command{
	command_name	env
	command_line	environment.pl -r $ARG1$ -u $ARG2$ -p $ARG3$ --wf $ARG4$ --cf $ARG5$ --wc $ARG6$ --cc $ARG7$ --wn $ARG8$ --cn $ARG9$
	}
to :
define command{
	command_name	env
	command_line	environment.pl -r $ARG1$ -u $ARG2$ -p $ARG3$ --wf $ARG4$ --cf $ARG5$ --wc $ARG6$ --cc $ARG7$ --wn 90 --cn 110
	}

note that in this case, you need to modify the host cfg file from:

define service{
        use                             generic-service         ; Name of service template to use
        host_name                       <routername>
        service_description             env
        check_command                   env!<ip:port>!<user!<password>!<warning fan threshold>!<critical fan threshold>!<warning chassis threshold>!<critical chassis threshold>!<warning npu threshold>!<critical npu threshold>
        }
to
define service{
        use                             generic-service         ; Name of service template to use
        host_name                       <routername>
        service_description             env
        check_command                   env!<ip:port>!<user!<password>!<warning fan threshold>!<critical fan threshold>!<warning chassis threshold>!<critical chassis threshold>
        }

to proceed with installation, complete steps below:

cp solace.cfg to /etc/nagios-plugins/config/
copy the plugins to the plugins directory.
cp *.pl to /usr/lib/nagios/plugins/
chmod +x /usr/lib/nagios/plugins/*.pl
chown nagios:nagios /usr/lib/nagios/plugins/*.pl
modify template for let say myrouter and copy it to nagios conf directory :
cp solace_host_template_nagios2.cfg .. to /etc/nagios3/conf.d/myrouter_nagios2.cfg
restart nagios with sudo service nagios restart or sudo /etc/init.d/nagios restart
